00:56:03.580 --> 00:56:08.460
Last summer, I had the pleasure
of meeting Tommy in Paris.

00:56:08.460 --> 00:56:09.960
That's actually the
entire anecdote.

00:56:09.960 --> 00:56:12.060
I just wanted to say we
saw each other in Paris.

00:56:12.060 --> 00:56:13.200
I think we should all
have the opportunity

00:56:13.200 --> 00:56:14.575
at one point in
our lives to say,

00:56:14.575 --> 00:56:17.010
we saw each other in Paris.

00:56:17.010 --> 00:56:19.600
It's like something that
Ernest Hemingway would say--

00:56:19.600 --> 00:56:26.810
saw Spot, Gertrude, Alice,
on the [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]..

00:56:26.810 --> 00:56:28.560
I'm taking adult French
classes right now,

00:56:28.560 --> 00:56:30.100
just want to show that off.

00:56:30.100 --> 00:56:31.230
[LAUGHTER]

00:56:31.230 --> 00:56:33.910
Hemingway has certainly been
on my mind for a long time.

00:56:33.910 --> 00:56:35.430
I remember when I was 18.

00:56:35.430 --> 00:56:39.240
